class Solution {
    public int countSegments(String s) {
        s = s.trim();
        if (s.isEmpty()) return 0;
        return s.split("\\s+").length;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution trims the input string to remove leading and trailing spaces, then splits it into segments using one or more spaces as the delimiter. It returns the number of resulting segments. The main strength is its simplicity and effectiveness in handling edge cases. 
